# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw config status reports (frac-0046): `promptclaw/config.py` now exposes a frozen `ConfigStatusReport` plus typed helpers `enabled_agents`, `config_status_report`, `summarize_config`, and `load_or_default` so callers can inspect the project name, artifact root, control-plane mode/agent, default task type, agent count, sorted enabled/disabled agent name tuples, and validation issues in one diagnostic call. `enabled_agents` returns deterministic alphabetical names; `summarize_config` is JSON-safe and exposes lists rather than tuples; `load_or_default` returns the persisted config when `promptclaw.json` is present and otherwise returns `default_project_config(project_name)` without writing to disk. Existing `default_project_config`, `config_path`, `load_config`, `save_config`, and `validate_config` signatures and behavior are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_config_depth.py` pins enabled-agent ordering, default and invalid-config status reports, JSON-safe summary lists, the load-or-default branch, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_config.py` remains the regression anchor for existing load/validate behavior.

- Added depth-2 composer quote verification reports (frac-0045): `my-claw/tools/composer_quote_verify.py` now exposes a frozen `QuoteVerificationReport` plus typed helpers `build_quote_verification_report`, `summarize_quote_verification_report`, `render_quote_verification_lines`, and `quote_verification_exit_code` around the existing hardware-free known-room/self-quote smoke path. The report captures descriptor identity/tags, requested/captured piece counts, song ids, match details, overlap, score, and status while preserving `trigger_composer_pieces`, `find_motif_tag_match`, and the CLI's existing success/failure output and exit codes. `tests/test_composer_quote_verify_depth.py` pins the end-to-end report, JSON-safe summary, CLI line rendering, failure-status exit mapping, and fractal depth >= 2; original composer quote, sample capture, self-listener, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 hook schema rewriter (frac-0044): `rewrite_hook.py` is now an importable module with a frozen `HookRewriteResult` dataclass plus typed helpers `apply_field_renames`, `migrate_file`, `apply_hook_rewrites`, and `main`, sourced from a canonical `HOOK_FIELD_RENAMES` table (`("hook_type", "hook_class")`, `("rhythm_cell", "rhythm")`) and `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` listing the five SenseWeave files the original one-shot script wrote to. The previous body of unconditional regex/`str.replace` calls — which left an already-migrated tree corrupted with duplicate dataclass fields and a broken `return HookProfile(...)` block when re-run — is replaced by an idempotent rename: `apply_field_renames` is pure string-in/string-out, `migrate_file` only writes when the produced text differs from disk and reports `existed`/`changed`, missing files report `existed=False` without raising, and `apply_hook_rewrites(root)` walks `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` in declared order returning one `HookRewriteResult` per target. `main()` prints a `rewrote`/`unchanged`/`missing` line per result and exits 0; `if __name__ == "__main__"` is preserved. `tests/test_rewrite_hook_depth.py` pins canonical-rename, idempotency, write-on-change, no-op-on-migrated-file, missing-file handling, declared-order tree migration, end-to-end idempotency on a migrated tree, the canonical rename table, and fractal depth >= 2; senseweave hook tests remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifact run reports (frac-0043): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes frozen `ArtifactFileStatus` and `ArtifactRunReport` dataclasses plus `ArtifactManager.build_run_report()` so callers can summarize expected run files, present/missing counts, missing file names, event count, and latest event type from the canonical `ProjectPaths.run_layout()` and existing event log. Existing artifact write helpers, `read_events()`, JSONL event shape, and on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` filenames are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_report.py` pins written-artifact summaries, JSON-safe report output, and fractal depth >= 2; existing artifact depth tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw SDP cost roll-ups (frac-0042): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` now exposes `total_cost_usd()`, `cost_by_model()`, `aggregate_rows()`, and `summarize_cost_run()` plus a frozen `CostRunSummary` dataclass so operator/CI callers can compute summed daily cost, partition cost across declared model tiers (with rows whose `models` list is empty bucketed under `fallback`, matching `match_pricing`'s sentinel), aggregate runs / token columns / cost into a single `DailyCostRow`, and run extract → CSV write → optional Markdown cap summary in one call. Existing `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, `write_csv`, `read_csv`, `check_daily_caps`, `summarize_daily_cap`, `render_cap_summary`, `write_cap_summary`, `_parse_args`, and `main` signatures, the on-disk CSV header, and the committed cap summary output are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_sdp_cost_depth.py` pins total / by-model / aggregate roll-ups, end-to-end CSV+cap output, the no-cap-path branch, public-surface preservation, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` and `tests/test_sdp_telemetry_cost_model.py` remain the regression anchors for extractor pricing and CLI behavior.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw path layouts (frac-0041): `promptclaw/paths.py` now exposes a frozen `RunPathLayout` plus `ProjectPaths.run_layout()`, `ProjectPaths.ensure_run_layout()`, and `ProjectPaths.path_summary()` so project/run filesystem contracts can produce typed layouts, idempotently prepare run directories, and emit JSON-safe operator summaries. Existing project-level path attributes and `run_*` helper return values are preserved; `ArtifactManager.create_run_layout()` now iterates the canonical run layout while keeping the same on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` structure. Empty run ids fail fast with `ValueError` before layout creation. `tests/test_promptclaw_paths_depth.py` pins helper compatibility, JSON-safe summaries, layout preparation through `ArtifactManager`, run-id rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; config, orchestrator, artifact, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifacts read path (frac-0040): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes `ArtifactManager.read_events()` which parses `events.jsonl` line by line and reconstructs the same `Event` dataclass shape that `append_event()` writes, returning `[]` when the log file does not yet exist. The four filename-taking write helpers (`write_prompt`, `write_output`, `write_handoff`, `write_summary`) now reject empty/whitespace-only filenames with `ValueError` before any I/O, matching the orchestrator's existing call-site contract while failing fast at the boundary. Existing public method signatures, on-disk filenames, JSONL serialization shape, and orchestrator call sites are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_depth.py` pins the round-trip read, missing-log empty result, empty-filename rejection across the four filename helpers, normal-filename acceptance, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_orchestrator.py` and `tests/test_config.py` remain the regression anchors for end-to-end run behavior and config loading.

